text: _Okay, this is not... I mean, this isn't... I'm not... Look, here's the thing, just 'cause _*_Horrible Bosses_*_ crew is behind this, I'll watch it. Horrible Bosses is one of my favorite comedy movies ever and I binge watch it time to time. I like Dwayne Johnson a lot (_*_shoutout to all wrestling fans out there!_*_) and I just love Alexandra Daddario. The kid has kind of grown on me, probably thanks to Seth Rogen. And I can't seem to fully accept Priyanka in all this for some reason. The funny thing is, I don't hate her. I've watched a few movies and I've liked quite a few of them tbh. I'm sure she's doing an excellent job in _*_Quintico_*_, as I haven't really had the time to watch it yet, but I read a lot, and I'm pretty sure I'd like it whenever I get to watch it. All that being said, I still can't accept her in Baywatch. It turned the whole thing to look like, a typical "big budget" Bollywood flick. And before making my point of all this, again I say, I will watch this movie. But this is not Baywatch, buddy. I'm sorry. I know you've wasted like a shit ton of money making this, but this just isn't the Baywatch i fell in love with back in the days. And the point of the classic show was never "Comedy," it was so much more than that. I'm a 80's kid and I know what Baywatch really is and you can't show me this shit and tell me it comes even close to the original. But the truth is, all of the mislead teenagers of this generation is probably going to get crazy over this and make it something bigger than what it really is. And then Hollywood would start making a bunch of drag-ass sequel/prequels. There goes our sweet ol' Baywatch down the comode and husshh' for the next generation. They will never know the true beauty of the classic show. Sad! (_*_shoutout to all Trump haters out there!_*_)_   _Bring back something right Hollywood, that's all I ask as a fellow movie/series snob. Anyone reading this, thanks for your precious time. If I stroked anyone's ego by saying all this, I apologise. I don't say much online, but when I do, I talk facts. I'm a very open minded and sarcastic person. Think about that before and if you comment. Have a great day stranger! - _*_Lunr_*
